summary: Tiger Woods: Masters win follows career doubts and changes children's perspective
body:
Tiger Woods: Masters win follows career doubts and changes children’s perspective

I’m actually pleased for him.

In my opinion, his vicissitudes were pretty much self-inflicted. He had the world at his feet, but it wasn’t enough, and he went off the rails.

The fact that he can put himself back on the right track and win a major again, eleven years after his last one, is a testament to what human beings can do when they put their minds to it.
